Description: At 4:35 p.m. MDT, Environment Canada meteorologists are tracking a severe thunderstorm capable of producing very strong wind gusts, toonie to ping pong ball size hail and heavy rain. Description: At 6:12 p.m. CST, Environment Canada meteorologists are tracking a severe thunderstorm that is possibly producing a tornado. Tornado warnings are issued when imminent or occurring thunderstorms are likely to produce or are producing tornadoes.
